args: Confirming influx of data to visual circuit.\nSubject's consciousness accessed.\n▷What are we looking at here?◁
Likely an image created from accumulated\npast data in Ayaha's consciousness.\n▷So it's her memories, basically.◁
Demons! The twin demons have appeared!
Those girls from the island nation?\nI thought they'd been driven off\nto the mountains!
They're wearing strange masks and burning\nhouses one after the—AAAAUGH!!
We'll be it, so you people run away.\nKya ha ha ha!
And if we catch you, you'll go through\nsome unsightly stuff—just like all of you\ndid to us! Kyaaa ha ha ha ha!
Been a while, huh? Also, you suuuure\nmade us put up with a lot of crap.
＂Don't go out.＂ ＂Don't play with anyone.＂\n＂Behave yourselves.＂ ＂Do what I say.＂\n＂Don't go around wherever you want.＂
All we ever got from you were toy dolls.\nYou did nothing else for us.
Having to follow your orders was\nREALLY tedious and boring.
You two have had supernatural power\nsince birth. What you see as play could\nvery well destroy everything.

As such, I hid you from society in an effort
to prevent everything around you from
coming to harm. But this is you two we're
talking about, so...

So we broke your word and played
outside, and then we broke that old
mercenary who used to come by
and play with us.

We weren't TRYING to break him!
We just heard he was strong and hit him
with all we had. Not our fault he was
actually super fragile.
Then you should understand why the two\nof you were banished from the village.\nThis resentment of yours is unjustifiable.
Yeah, we thought we did something bad.\nWe disobeyed your command, after all.
That's why we thought it made sense\nthat you and the villagers chased us into\nthe mountains.
It was our fault that we were hungry.\nIt was our fault our clothes were dirty.\nIt was all our fault. All of it.
But then he taught us that was wrong.
He told us that people with power\ncould use it to gain their freedom.
We have power, which means we have\nfreedom. So what we do is up to us.
We won't be bound by anyone else's\ndecisions. We'll play how we like and\nnot let anyone ever yell at us again.
Our freedom won't be interfered with.\nAnd now we're going to play with the ones\nwho tried to take our freedom away.
—Kyaaaa ha ha ha!\n—Eh heh heh heh!
This is no freedom. True freedom is made\nby coming to an understanding with others.
You two are beasts who can't be reasoned\nwith, and I should have killed you when\nI had the chance!
Trying to do the whole ＂parent＂ thing too\nlate in the game and lecture us, I guess.\nHow tedious.
I'm the only one who can call her Oto.\nIsn't that right, Oto?
That's right, Aya. There's no one else.\nSince the moment we were born, I've had\na connection with no one but you.
Uninhibited conflagration...\nJust as I expected, you're making full use\nof the mask's power.
Hey, our freedom is the most right, right?
The strong decide what is right. If you\nbelieve your freedom is right, use your\npower to prove this is the case.
Yeah! If anyone denies our freedom,\nwe'll teach 'em how wrong they are!
And don't forget my request. Now that\nyou're wearing the masks, you two are\nrebels against this world.
Oh, we'll help with that. We wanna destroy\nthis stifling world as bad as you do!
We are wings. Paired, free,\nsoaring over all. We are Agito!
This is how they ended up joining Agito.\n▷For better or worse, these kids are about\nas pure and genuine as you get.◁

Mascula, we need to prioritize gathering
information. We'll search her memories
of the Sacred Tree and find out what
became of the other Agito members.
Imagery of defeated Agitos located.\nThis seems to be a memory that took\nplace after the fight at the Sacred Tree.
▷Speaking of that, I've been wondering\nabout something. When we fought them\nhere, they couldn't speak...◁
After losing to you, they swore revenge and\nsought to amplify the power of the masks\nthey had been given.

They bolstered their fighting instincts to
the very limits of their control, and as part
of that process limited even their ability
to communicate.
▷But just a while ago, Ayaha was\ncommunicating normally. So what's\nthe deal with that?◁
Ayaha said she lost the mask's power,\nwhich likely stifled her own ability.
▷I wonder if because she lost her power,\nshe was freed from that particular effect.\n...Oh!◁

▷The Agito members were caught up
in the Sacred Tree's collapse!◁
Target lost. I can't confirm if they're alive
or dead.
▷No, wait. I see a figure in the smoke.\nIs that...?◁
Nobody's gonna mess up our freedom.
▷Did you see that, Laxi?◁\nThe power of their mask...
I'm gonna crush you between my teeth!\nAaaah ha ha ha ha!
